1)About CUDA(Compute Unified Device Architecture)
   Think of CUDA as the translator and control system that helps your program use an NVIDIA GPU properly. 
   The GPU is the fast worker, and CUDA is the instruction set that tells that worker how to do many jobs at the same time.
   So if your program has a big job, CUDA helps move the heavy part to the GPU so it can finish faster.
   That is why CUDA is commonly used for training machine learning models, image processing, and other tasks with lots of repeated calculations.
